%3E%3Cu%3Ecomprehensive%20database%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20origins%20and%20fates%20of%2050%20million%20American%20companies.%20Which%20ones%2C%20they%20wanted%20to%20know%2C%20became%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-employees-number-1-of-153-us-workers-head-count-2021-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Elargest%20employers%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20their%20industries%3F%20Which%20ones%20%3Cem%3Esucceeded%3C%2Fem%3E%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20team's%20leader%2C%20John%20Haltiwanger%2C%20is%20an%20economist%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Maryland%20who%20studies%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fa16z-hires-daniel-penny-marine-veteran-cleared-subway-death-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Edynamism%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%20That%20means%20he%20seeks%20to%20understand%20changes%20over%20time%20%E2%80%94%20why%20some%20things%20surge%20while%20other%20things%20flame%20out.%20He%20and%20his%20team%20looked%20at%20the%20lifespan%20of%20American%20companies%20founded%20from%201981%20to%202022.%20They%20examined%20an%20impressive%20range%20of%20factors%3A%20owner%20demographics%2C%20management%20structure%2C%20startup%20financing%2C%20profitability%2C%20even%20the%20aspirations%20of%20the%20founders.%20It's%20nothing%20less%20than%20a%20complete%20accounting%20of%20what%20turns%20a%20business%20into%20a%20behemoth%20%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3Bthe%20best%20database%20in%20town%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20Haltiwanger%20puts%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20O%20great%20and%20powerful%20database%2C%20what%20makes%20the%20numbers%20go%20up%20and%20to%20the%20right%3F%20What%20makes%20a%20company%20successful%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20answer%20%E2%80%94%20you%20will%20be%20shocked%20to%20hear%20%E2%80%94%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvcs-2023-startup-fundraising-challenges-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Emoney%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20strongest%20correlation%20between%20business%20success%20and%20the%20factors%20Haltiwanger%20analyzed%20is%20how%20much%20financing%20a%20company%20is%20able%20to%20raise%20before%20it%20launches.%20Starting%20with%20%241%20million%20boosts%20the%20probability%20of%20success%20by%20a%20whopping%2025%20percentage%20points.%20It's%20like%20the%20old%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fonly-murders-in-the-building-steve-martin-martin-short-games-2022-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ESteve%20Martin%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20joke%3A%20%3Cem%3EHere's%20how%20to%20become%20a%20millionaire%3A%20First%2C%20get%20a%20million%20dollars.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Haltiwanger%20found%20that%20it%20also%20matters%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-bootstrap-startup-to-success-according-to-founders%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Ewhere%20%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cu%3Ethe%20money%20comes%20from%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20If%20you%20self-finance%20with%20credit%20cards%2C%20your%20chances%20of%20success%20actually%20%3Cem%3Edecrease%20%3C%2Fem%3Eby%202%20points.%20If%20you%20get%20a%20loan%20from%20a%20bank%2C%20your%20chances%20improve%20by%209%20points%20%E2%80%94%20but%20that's%20been%20harder%20and%20harder%20to%20do%20over%20the%20past%20couple%20of%20decades.%20So%20the%20best%20bet%20is%20if%20you're%20backed%20by%20venture%20capital%3A%20VC%20investment%20increases%20your%20chance%20of%20success%20by%205%20points.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJust%20as%20Silicon%20Valley%20is%20always%20boasting%2C%20venture-backed%20startups%20really%20have%20been%20the%20most%20economically%20dynamic%20and%20productive%20companies%20in%20America.%20They%20have%20the%20most%20innovation%2C%20the%20most%20patents%2C%20the%20biggest%20R%26amp%3BD%20budgets.%20And%20they%20have%20often%20grown%20to%20have%20the%20most%20employees%20%E2%80%94%20the%20metric%20that%20Haltiwanger's%20team%20used%20to%20indicate%20success.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20therein%20lies%20a%20problem%3A%20Almost%20no%20one%20gets%20venture%20capital.%20Of%20the%201.5%20million%20companies%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.americanprogress.org%2Farticle%2Fentrepreneurship-startups-and-business-formation-are-booming-across-the-u-s%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Elaunch%20every%20year%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20only%20a%20few%20thousand%20are%20blessed%20with%20VC%20investment.%20And%20the%20best%20way%20to%20get%20venture%20capital%2C%20Haltiwanger%20found%2C%20is%20to%20be%20a%20young%2C%20white%20man.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20Haltiwanger%20isn't%20the%20first%20to%20discover%20venture%20capital's%20built-in%20bias.%20As%20I've%20written%2C%20VCs%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwomen-in-vc-partner-promotions-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Emostly%20white%20and%20mostly%20male%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20they%20tend%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpitching-silicon-valley-investors-research-funding-science-vibe-data-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Egive%20money%20to%20people%20they%20know%20and%20like%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20turn%20out%20to%20also%20be%20mostly%20white%20and%20male.%20Last%20year%2C%20four%20out%20of%20every%20five%20venture%20deals%20went%20to%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpitchbook.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Ffemale-founders-just-took-in-their-smallest-share-of-vc-deals-in-five-years%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eall-male%20founder%20team%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Haltiwanger's%20study%20confirms%20the%20pattern.%20Women%20and%20nonwhite%20owners%2C%20he%20found%2C%20are%20less%20likely%20to%20have%20outside%20investors%20%E2%80%94%20and%20young%20founders%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20have%20them.%20The%20secret%20to%20succeeding%20in%20business%2C%20the%20data%20shows%2C%20essentially%20boils%20down%20to%3A%20Be%20a%20tech%20bro%20who%20gets%20money%20from%20other%20tech%20bros.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20so%20much%20that%20has%20to%20go%20right%20for%20you%20to%20be%20successful%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Florian%20Ederer%2C%20an%20economist%20at%20Boston%20University%20who%20studies%20startups.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20always%20going%20to%20privilege%20people%20with%20better%20networks%20and%20better%20initial%20starting%20conditions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EI%20know!%20Not%20great.%20The%20data%20confirms%20the%20lived%20experience%20of%20millions%20of%20entrepreneurs%3A%20The%20richer%20you%20start%20off%2C%20the%20richer%20you're%20likely%20to%20get.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Haltiwanger%20hopes%20to%20use%20his%20database%20to%20answer%20a%20question%20even%20deeper%20than%20why%20some%20companies%20succeed.%20That%20is%2C%20why%20more%20and%20more%20companies%20%3Cem%3Edon't%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Haltiwanger's%20data%20shows%20that%20the%20legendary%20energy%20of%20Silicon%20Valley%20startups%20%E2%80%94%20the%20origin%20story%20of%20a%20couple%20of%20geniuses%20back%20in%20the%201980s%20building%20something%20in%20a%20garage%20that%20metastasized%20into%20an%20Apple%20or%20a%20Microsoft%20or%20a%20Google%20%E2%80%94%20well%2C%20that%20just%20isn't%20happening%20much%20anymore.%20The%20VC%20money%20is%20still%20there%3B%20the%20dynamism%20ain't.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYoung%2C%20fast%20companies%20used%20to%20be%20major%20sources%20of%20employment.%20In%201981%2C%2015%25%20of%20working%20Americans%20were%20employed%20at%20companies%20four%20years%20old%20or%20younger.%20In%202022%2C%20Haltiwanger's%20team%20found%2C%20it%20was%20down%20to%20only%209%25.%20And%20those%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fdx.doi.org%2F10.1016%2Fj.euroecorev.2015.12.013%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ecompanies%20aren't%20growing%20as%20fast%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20they%20used%20to.%20In%201999%2C%20the%20most%20dynamic%20companies%20outstripped%20the%20median%20rate%20of%20growth%20by%2030%25.%20By%202012%2C%20they%20were%20expanding%20at%20pretty%20much%20the%20same%20rate%20as%20other%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20tech%20sector%20were%20as%20dynamic%20as%20it%20was%20back%20in%20the%201990s%2C%20when%20a%20cohort%20of%20startups%20grew%20into%20Big%20Tech%2C%20it%20would%20be%20sending%20a%20constant%20stream%20of%20new%20challengers%20onto%20the%20field.%20But%20that%20hasn't%20happened.%20%26quot%3BHave%20we%20seen%20a%20remarkable%20cohort%20like%20that%20in%20a%20while%3F%26quot%3B%20Haltiwanger%20says.%20%26quot%3BThe%20answer%20is%20no%20%E2%80%94%20and%20we%20don't%20know%20why.%26quot%3B%20Figuring%20that%20out%2C%20he%20adds%2C%20will%20take%20some%20more%20number%20crunching.%20But%20he%20has%20some%20theories.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ETheory%20No.%201%3A%20%3C%2Fem%3EMaybe%20people%20are%20starting%20different%20kinds%20of%20small%20businesses%20nowadays%20%E2%80%94%20not%20high-tech%20firms%2C%20but%20things%20like%20restaurants%20and%20pool%20cleaner%20services%20and%20yoga%20studios.%20Those%20businesses%20are%20more%20likely%20than%20tech%20firms%20to%20be%20owned%20by%20women%20and%20people%20of%20color.%20From%202002%20to%202021%2C%20Haltiwanger%20found%2C%20the%20share%20of%20young%20companies%20run%20by%20women%20rose%20from%2010%25%20to%2018%25%2C%20while%20those%20run%20by%20people%20of%20color%20jumped%20from%2010%25%20to%2027%25.%20But%20those%20owners%20almost%20never%20get%20venture%20funding%2C%20and%20they're%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fquickbooks.intuit.com%2Fr%2Fsmall-business-data%2Findex-annual-report-2025%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Emore%20likely%20to%20self-finance%20with%20credit%20cards%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20So%20they're%20less%20likely%20to%20get%20big%2C%20the%20way%20tech%20companies%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ETheory%20No.%202%3A%20%3C%2Fem%3ENow%20that%20a%20handful%20of%20companies%20like%20Google%20and%20Meta%20dominate%20the%20tech%20landscape%2C%20maybe%20the%20kind%20of%20people%20who%20might%20otherwise%20have%20been%20hard-charging%20founders%20are%20instead%20getting%20high-paying%2C%20low-stress%20gigs%20in%20Big%20Tech.%20After%20all%2C%20the%20older%2C%20slower-growing%20companies%20are%20where%20the%20jobs%20are.%20Small%20businesses%20got%20less%20dynamic%2C%20in%20other%20words%2C%20because%20a%20few%20big%20companies%20now%20employ%20all%20the%20aspiring%20dynamos.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ETheory%20No.%203%3A%20%3C%2Fem%3EBig%20Tech%20companies%20aren't%20just%20employing%20all%20the%20talent%20%E2%80%94%20they're%20also%20buying%20up%20all%20the%20most%20promising%20startups.%20In%20the%20late%201980s%20and%20early%201990s%2C%20innovative%20startups%20were%20more%20likely%20to%20go%20public%20than%20get%20purchased%3B%20by%202001%2C%20the%20reverse%20was%20true.%20In%202019%2C%20there%20were%20only%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fssrn.com%2Fabstract%3D4322834%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E100%20IPOs%20%E2%80%94%20compared%20with%20900%20acquisitions%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Most%20of%20the%20startups%20were%20bought%20by%20the%20half-dozen%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbig-tech-sabotages-new-startups-businesses-coopting-disruption-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EBig%20Tech%20companies%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20you'd%20expect.%20The%20newbies%20didn't%20get%20big.%20They%20got%20eaten.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20question%20Haltiwanger%20is%20asking%20%E2%80%94%20why%20young%20companies%20aren't%20growing%20as%20fast%20as%20they%20used%20to%20%E2%80%94%20is%20an%20important%20one.%20Before%202000%2C%20when%20businesses%20were%20able%20to%20get%20bigger%2C%20America's%20aggregate%20productivity%20growth%20was%20a%20bit%20more%20than%202%25.%20Since%20then%2C%20it's%20more%20like%201%25.%20Less%20dynamism%20acts%20as%20a%20brake%20on%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20it's%20possible%20that%20all%20those%20little%20startups%20swallowed%20by%20the%20bigger%20companies%20are%20still%20creating%20intellectual%20property%20and%20jobs%20and%20new%20products%2C%20goosing%20the%20economy%20in%20ways%20the%20numbers%20have%20missed.%20%26quot%3BThe%20evidence%20is%20not%20definitive%20yet.%20That's%20something%20we%20want%20to%20go%20investigate%2C%26quot%3B%20Haltiwanger%20says.%20%26quot%3BBut%20if%20innovation%20was%20proceeding%20in%20the%20same%20way%20as%20before%20%E2%80%94%20startups%20were%20contributing%20as%20much%20as%20they%20did%20before%2C%20just%20in%20a%20different%20way%20%E2%80%94%20then%20why%20is%20productivity%20growth%20so%20low%3F%20Something%20has%20changed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EWhich%20brings%20us%20to%20Theory%20No.%204.%20Maybe%2C%20Haltiwanger%20thinks%2C%20the%20lull%20in%20business%20growth%20is%20a%20%3Cem%3Egood%20%3C%2Fem%3Ething.%20Maybe%2C%20just%20maybe%2C%20it's%20the%20calm%20before%20the%20innovative%20storm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20conventional%20story%2C%20as%20told%20by%20Silicon%20Valley%2C%20is%20that%20tech%20startups%20got%20big%20thanks%20to%20the%20bold%2C%20risk-taking%20vision%20of%20the%20venture%20capitalists%20backing%20them.%20Haltiwanger%20thinks%20it's%20more%20complicated%20than%20that.%20For%20one%20thing%2C%20startup-driven%20productivity%20and%20tech%20innovation%20happened%20long%20before%20the%20invention%20of%20modern%20venture%20capital.%20And%20for%20another%2C%20periods%20of%20innovation%20are%20usually%20preceded%20by%20a%20noticeable%20lag%20in%20growth.%20Go%20back%20and%20look%20at%20industries%20that%20boomed%20in%20the%20past%20century%20%E2%80%94%20chemicals%2C%20cars%2C%20robotics%20%E2%80%94%20and%20you%20see%20that%20there's%20a%20period%20of%20dormancy%20before%20the%20new%20tech%20gets%20implemented%20at%20scale.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EStartups%20quietly%20work%20out%20the%20kinks%20in%20their%20crazy%20ideas%2C%20bursting%20forth%20like%20cicadas%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ewhen%20the%20tech%20is%20ready.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20that's%20true%2C%20Haltiwanger%20theorizes%2C%20maybe%20the%20current%20slump%20in%20business%20growth%20is%20a%20signal%20of%20a%20boom%20to%20come.%20And%20maybe%20this%20time%20around%2C%20the%20new%20tech%20that's%20about%20to%20explode%20on%20the%20scene%20is%20artificial%20intelligence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20clearly%20seeing%20a%20surge%20in%20startups%20in%20the%20last%20few%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20Haltiwanger%20says.%20%26quot%3BWe%20see%20in%20the%20data%20that%20it%20is%20closely%20tied%20to%20AI.%20The%20really%20hard%20question%20is%3A%20Is%20this%20a%20new%20platform%2C%20a%20pathbreaking%20change%20in%20the%20way%20we%20do%20business%20and%20the%20way%20we%20work%20and%20how%20we%20live%3F%20Or%20is%20it%20not%20going%20to%20have%20the%20same%20kick%20as%20IT%3F%26quot%3B%20That's%20what%20Haltiwanger%20is%20looking%20to%20answer%20with%20his%20monster%20database.%20The%20productivity%20slowdown%20of%20the%20past%2010%20years%20might%20just%20be%20the%20shakedown%20period%20before%20an%20explosion%20of%20nifty%20new%20AI%20stuff%2C%20and%20we'll%20experience%20another%20period%20of%20dynamism.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20explosions%20also%20cause%20a%20lot%20of%20damage.%20Cheaper%20and%20lighter%20AI%20systems%20from%20China%20like%20DeepSeek%20could%20nullify%20the%20capital-intensive%20machinations%20of%20wannabe%20incumbents%20like%20OpenAI.%20Or%20AI%20could%20eliminate%20millions%20of%20jobs%2C%20sparking%20all%20sorts%20of%20economic%20upheaval.%20Or%20the%20most%20innovative%20AI%20startups%20could%20get%20consumed%20by%20the%20Microsofts%20and%20Googles%20before%20they're%20able%20to%20grow%20into%20tech%20giants%20of%20their%20own.%20The%20economy%20might%20get%20more%20dynamic%20with%20the%20rise%20of%20AI.%20But%20if%20the%20new%20technology%20moves%20fast%20and%20breaks%20things%2C%20as%20so%20many%20of%20its%20predecessors%20have%2C%20will%20that%20still%20count%20as%20success%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fadam-rogers%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EAdam%20Rogers%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsuccessful-businesses-secret-funding-job-company-growth-money-financing-startups-2025-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1740992642000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67c0aa0fb8b41a9673f932cb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsuccessful-businesses-secret-funding-job-company-growth-money-financing-startups-2025-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20study%20of%2050%20million%20companies%20reveals%20why%20some%20thrive%20%E2%80%94%20and%20others%20fail%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22arogers%40businessinsider.com%20(Adam%20Rogers)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsuccessful-businesses-secret-funding-job-company-growth-money-financing-startups-2025-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22HC%20relief%20for%20ex-Sebi%20chief%20Buch%2C%20halts%20ACB%20action%20until%20March%204%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1740992505000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-118681108%2Cimgsize-1645568.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fstock-market-fraud-case-bombay-hc-grants-relief-to-ex-sebi-chief-buch-halts-acb-action-until-march-4%2Farticleshow%2F118681123.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Bombay%20High%20Court%20granted%20relief%20to%20former%20SEBI%20chairperson%20Madhabi%20Puri%20Buch%20and%20five%20other%20officials%2C%20instructing%20the%20ACB%20not%20to%20file%20an%20FIR%20against%20them%20until%20March%204.%20This%20fol