rable%20reputational%20damage%20to%20Washington's%20soft%20and%20hard%20powers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThirdly%2C%20by%20publicly%20bullying%20an%20invited%20Head%20of%20State%20in%20a%20petulant%20and%20subjective%20manner%2C%20the%20US%20has%20cast%20itself%20as%20an%20unpredictable%20patron%20and%20volatile%20negotiator.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELastly%2C%20it%20does%20little%20to%20dignify%20the%20image%20of%20a%20presumed%20hyperpower%20if%20its%20Head%20of%20State%20is%20seen%20in%20a%20slanging%20match%20with%20a%20disproportionately%20smaller%20interlocutor.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ETrump's%20Freudian%20Slips%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20a%20personal%20level%2C%20Trump%20stood%20damaged%20by%20his%20several%20Freudian%20Slips%20on%20display%20at%20the%20White%20House%20by%20the%20unwitting%20rekindling%20of%20the%20controversies%20that%20dogged%20Trump%201.0.%20His%20public%20upbraiding%20of%20Zelensky%20on%20February%2028%20at%20the%20White%20House%20can%20be%20seen%20as%20a%20payback%20for%20an%20impeachment%20trial%20by%20the%20US%20Congress.%20In%202019%2C%20Trump%20was%20accused%20of%20phoning%20Zelensky%20to%20ask%20for%20launching%20an%20investigation%20against%20the%20son%20of%20Joe%20Biden%20his%20presumed%20Democratic%20opponent%20at%20the%20approaching%20elections%2C%20then%20working%20with%20a%20Ukrainian%20company%2C%20as%20a%20pre-condition%20to%20get%20%24400%20million%20in%20American%20military%20assistance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurther%2C%20his%20emotive%20and%20stout%20defence%20of%20Russian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%20(%E2%80%9Che%20went%20together%20a%20lot%20with%20me%E2%80%9D)%20also%20harks%20back%20to%20an%20FBI%20investigation%20into%20the%20swirling%20allegations%20of%20Russian%20interference%20in%20his%20favour%20in%20the%202016%20elections.%20While%20both%20these%20allegations%20were%20eventually%20dropped%2C%20Trump's%20reference%20to%20his%20past%20karmas%20during%20the%20White%20House%20spat%20%E2%80%93%20from%20settling%20scores%20with%20Zelensky%2C%20a%20visceral%20animus%20for%20his%20predecessor%20and%20defending%20Putin%20against%20domestic%20investigations%2C%20were%20self-goals%20likely%20to%20tainted%20him%20as%20a%20tempestuous%20maverick%20prone%20to%20mix%20his%20personal%20domestic%20agenda%20with%20national%20interest%20abroad.%20From%20now%20onwards%2C%20any%20steps%20he%20takes%20on%20the%20Ukraine-Russia%20conflict%2C%20including%20significant%20relaxation%20of%20the%2021%2C000-plus%20economic%20sanctions%20on%20Russia%2C%20may%20invite%20scrutiny%20about%20bias%20in%20favour%20of%20Russia%20and%20President%20Putin%20complicating%20his%20self-proclaimed%20neutrality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EPutin%20Is%20Not%20The%20Winner%20Here%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMost%20observers%20have%20loudly%20proclaimed%20Putin%20as%20the%20solitary%20winner%20of%20the%20Oval%20Office%20imbroglio.%20However%2C%20on%20a%20closer%20look%2C%20this%20conclusion%20appears%20questionable.%20Putin%20and%20Russian%20nationalists%20may%20gloat%20over%20a%20fall-out%20between%20Ukraine%20and%20United%20States%2C%20the%20hitherto%20chief%20mentor%20and%20sustainer%20of%20their%20opponent%20on%20the%20battlefield.%20But%20the%20episode%20pushes%20down%20the%20timeline%20for%20the%20end%20of%20the%20conflict%2C%20a%20priority%20for%20the%20Kremlin.%20It%20also%20makes%20easing%20of%20crippling%20economic%20sanctions%20less%20likely.%20In%20case%20the%20West%20Europeans%20take%20up%20the%20slack%20and%20reinvigorate%20the%20defence%20supplies%20to%20Kyiv%2C%20and%20create%20an%20autonomous%20anti-Russian%20defence%20alliance%2C%20this%20would%20disserve%20Moscow's%20interests.%20A%20united%20European%20defence%20bloc%20will%20be%20a%20formidable%20opponent%20with%20a%20combined%20GDP%2011%20times%20bigger%20than%20Russia's.%20It%20would%20have%20two%20nuclear%20powers%20each%20with%20permanent%20membership%20of%20the%20UN%20Security%20Council.%20Lastly%2C%20this%20continental%20repolarisation%20would%20also%20have%20opportunity%20costs%20for%20Moscow%20as%20prospects%20for%20an%20early%20post-war%20resumption%20of%20energy%20symbiosis%20would%20recede%20even%20further.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20Next%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20February%2028%20White%20House%20clash%20has%20pushed%20the%20Europeans%20towards%20their%20moment%20of%20truth%20as%20they%20face%20a%20Hobson's%20choice%20on%20two%20issues%3A%20the%20need%20to%20reverse%20their%20centrifugal%20tendencies%2C%20and%20collective%20militarisation%20against%20Putin's%20Russia%20perceived%20as%20an%20expansionist%20threat%20seeking%20to%20re-merge%20the%20former%20Soviet%20components.%20The%20EU%20economies%20have%20recorded%20an%20anaemic%20growth%20of%201.1%25%20in%202024%20and%20are%20likely%20to%20grow%20only%20by%201.6%25%20this%20year.%20They%20are%2C%20thus%2C%20in%20poor%20shape%20to%20rev%20up%20their%20defence%20expenditure%20in%20a%20sustainable%20manner%20and%20fill%20the%20gap%20voided%20by%20the%20US.%20While%20the%20London%20Summit%20on%20March%202%20showed%20an%20impressive%20NATO%20lineup%2C%20it%20still%20preferred%20to%20bring%20the%20US%20back%20into%20the%20alliance%20backing%20Ukraine%20%E2%80%93%20a%20prospect%20that%20may%20need%20time%20and%20selective%20amnesia%2C%20both%20in%20short%20supply%20amidst%20an%20unrelenting%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20a%20different%20level%2C%20other%20go-between%20peacemakers%2C%20such%20as%20Turkey%2C%20Saudi%20Arabia%20and%20the%20UAE%2C%20may%20strive%20to%20step%20into%20the%20void%20and%20offer%20to%20host%20multilateral%20talks%20to%20end%20the%20Russia-Ukraine%20war.%20However%2C%20the%20issue%20of%20the%20Washington-Moscow%20reset%20may%20then%20need%20to%20be%20dissociated%20from%20the%20Ukraine%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina%20has%20considerable%20stakes%20in%20the%20Russia-Ukraine%20war.%20On%20one%20hand%2C%20Beijing%20has%20leveraged%20the%20hostilities%20and%20resultant%20Russia's%20isolation%20to%20forge%20a%20%E2%80%9Cno-limit%E2%80%9D%20strategic%20partnership%20with%20Moscow.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20the%20Western%20preoccupation%20with%20Moscow%20has%20allowed%20China%20time%20and%20space%20to%20continue%20with%20its%20drive%20to%20dominate%20its%20neighbourhood.%20Thus%2C%20a%20jerky%20US-Ukraine%20and%20US-NATO%20partings%20may%20be%20a%20mixed%20blessing%20for%20Beijing.%20It%20may%20invite%20the%20unwelcomed%20resumption%20of%20Washington's%20%E2%80%98pivot%20Asia'%20policy%20to%20contain%20China.%20Further%2C%20any%20eventual%20normalisation%20of%20Russia's%20ties%20with%20the%20West%20may%20correspondingly%20reduce%20Moscow's%20ardour%20for%20Beijing.%20In%20case%20West%20Europe%20morphs%20into%20a%20defence%20bloc%2C%20the%20resultant%20multipolarity%20may%2C%20however%2C%20suit%20Beijing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20This%20Means%20For%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20%E2%80%93%20and%20much%20of%20the%20Global%20South%20%E2%80%93%20have%20been%20collateral%20victims%20of%20the%20three-year%20Ukraine%20crisis%2C%20facing%20supply%20chain%20disruption%20of%20global%20trade%20of%20vital%20commodities%20from%20foodstuff%20to%20hydrocarbons.%20They%20would%20have%20been%20dismayed%20at%20the%20White%20House%20spat%2C%20fearing%20it%20to%20prolong%20the%20crisis.%20The%20US%20fixation%20with%20%E2%80%9Csuch%20good%20friends%E2%80%9D%20as%20Ukraine%2C%20Israel%2C%20etc%20has%20often%20overridden%20its%20engagements%20with%20less%20pressing%20horizontal%20global%20issues%2C%20such%20as%20poverty%2C%20hunger%2C%20disease%2C%20climate%20change%2C%20energy%20and%20other%20regional%20tensions.%20The%20incident%20may%2C%20optimistically%2C%20allow%20the%20Trump%20Presidency%2C%20currently%20downsizing%20its%20foreign%20engagements%2C%20to%20correct%20its%20course%20both%20qualitatively%20and%20quantitatively.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESix%20weeks%20into%20Trump%202.0%2C%20the%20opening%20overture%20of%